  ],
  "forbidden_actions": [
    "Never do X because Y"
  ],
  "execution_rules": [
    "DO NOT retrieve long-term memory independently ŌĆö all memory context is in this packet",
    "DO NOT call MCP tools ŌĆö harness provided all context during planning",
    "DO NOT replan or modify the ExecutionPlan",
    "DO NOT expand scope beyond what is listed in scope statement"
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "step_number": 1,
      "title": "Step title from ExecutionPlan",
      "actions": ["Action 1", "Action 2"],
      "outputs": ["Output 1", "Output 2"],
      "acceptance_checks": ["Check 1", "Check 2"]
    }
  ],
  "required_output_sections": [
    "per_step_results",
    "final_deliverables",
    "validation_summary"
  ]
}
```

### Field Reference

| Field | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `worker_id` | YES | Unique identifier for this worker packet |
| `goal` | YES | Same as RequirementIntent.goal |
| `scope` | YES | Same as ExecutionPlan.scope |
| `hard_constraints` | YES | All constraints from RequirementIntent and ExecutionPlan |
| `forbidden_actions` | YES | All forbidden actions from ExecutionPlan |
| `execution_rules` | YES | Must include memory prohibition rules (see example above) |
| `steps` | YES | All steps from ExecutionPlan, in order |
| `required_output_sections` | YES | Must always be `["per_step_results", "final_deliverables", "validation_summary"]` |

### Example

See Stage 8 in harness_design.md section 8 for a complete example.

### Critical: Memory Prohibition

The `execution_rules` array MUST include:

```json
"execution_rules": [
  "DO NOT retrieve long-term memory independently ŌĆö all memory context is in this packet",
  "DO NOT call MCP tools ŌĆö harness provided all context during planning",
  "DO NOT replan or modify the ExecutionPlan",
  "DO NOT expand scope beyond what is listed in scope statement"
]
```

This is not optional. Harness validates that memory retrieval is explicitly forbidden.

### Submission Command

```powershell
.\harness\invoke-harness-control-plane.ps1 submit-step-result `
    -SessionId "<sessionId>" `
    -Action "agent_generate_worker_execution_packet" `
    -ArtifactType "WorkerExecutionPacket" `
    -ArtifactFile "worker_execution_packet.json"
```

