## Summary Checklist

When you're about to submit an artifact, verify:

### RequirementIntent
- [ ] Has `task_id`, `task_type`, `goal`, `hard_constraints`, `risk_signals`, `complexity`
- [ ] All fields present
- [ ] `task_type` is one of the allowed enum values
- [ ] `complexity` is exactly `low`, `medium`, or `high`

### RetrievalChunkSet
- [ ] Has `task_id`, `complexity`, `chunks`
- [ ] Has `core_task` chunk
- [ ] Has `constraint` chunk IF hard_constraints non-empty
- [ ] Has `risk` chunk IF risk_signals non-empty
- [ ] Has `similar_case` with `task_shape` IF complexity is `medium` or `high`
- [ ] All fields use snake_case

### ChunkQualityReport
- [ ] Has all boolean flags: `has_core_task`, `has_constraint`, `has_risk`, `has_pattern`, `has_similar_case`
- [ ] Flags are booleans, not strings
- [ ] Has `errors` and `warnings` arrays (can be empty)
- [ ] Flags match actual chunks in RetrievalChunkSet

### MCP Responses
- [ ] Submit RAW response from MCP tool
- [ ] Do NOT modify the response
- [ ] Do NOT extract or summarize fields

### ExecutionPlan
- [ ] All steps have `step_number`, `title`, `actions`, `outputs`, `acceptance_checks`
- [ ] `deliverables` is non-empty
- [ ] `forbidden_actions` is non-empty

### WorkerExecutionPacket
- [ ] `execution_rules` explicitly forbids memory retrieval and MCP calls
- [ ] `required_output_sections` is always `["per_step_results", "final_deliverables", "validation_summary"]`
- [ ] All fields present

